  "instructions": [
    "preheat oven to 400 degrees fahrenheit (200 degrees celsius).",
    "in a large bowl, combine flour, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper.",
    "add warm water and mix until dough forms.",
    "knead dough for 5 minutes until smooth.",
    "divided dough into 8 equal pieces and roll each piece into a ball.",
    "flatten each ball into a disk shape.",
    "place a tablespoon of mashed potatoes in the center of each disk.",
    "top with chopped cranberries, scallions, and cheddar cheese.",
    "brush edges with olive oil and fold empanadas in half to form a half-moon shape.",
    "brush tops with beaten egg for a golden glaze.",
    "place empanadas on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.",
    "fry empanadas in hot oil for 2-3 minutes on each side until crispy and golden."
  ],
